value.value: Clinical and laboratory findings about the umbilical cord.
A species of yeast-like fungus that is the causative organism of Pneumocystis pneumonia.

A species of dematiaceous filamentous fungi in the phylum Ascomycota with small, delicate annellides with a distinct basal swelling peculiar to this species and absent in closely related species. L. prolificans causes opportunistic infection in immunocompetent and immunosuppressed individuals. The species exhibits varying tolerance to currently available antifungal agents.
Change in umbilical cord color resulting from postmortem changes. It indicates fetal death occurred at least 6 hours prior to delivery.
Meconium staining of the fetal membrane.
An observation that the fetal membranes are inserted at the edge of the placental disc.
The space that occupies the distance between the shortest free edge of the fetal membranes and the disc edge.
A maternal placental surface that is smooth and without appreciable parenchymal loss.
A maternal placental surface that lacks a smooth basal plate. Missing pieces of the placental parenchyma are appreciable.
The typical uniform coloring of the placental parenchyma irrespective of gestational age.
The variable or non-uniform coloring of the placental parenchyma indicating variable contribution of the blood contained within the fetal vessels to the color of the parenchyma.
A separation of the placenta from the uterine wall that is manifested by a retroplacental hematoma with villous compression and change in villous coloration that is reflective of lesion age.
Macroscopically identifiable placental parenchymal abnormality.
A character or string that represents the information contained in a data field.
A description of the value that describes missing data, eg. unknown, not applicable.
The textual description of the terminology system that is being used.
The version information of the terminology system that is being used.

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA Body System or Organ Class Code

value.value: A coded value specifying the type of body system or organ class related to the adverse event from the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA).

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA High Level Group Term

value.value: A superordinate descriptor for one or more Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA) high level terms (HLT) for the adverse event.

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA High Level Group Term Code

value.value: A coded value specifying the high level group term for the adverse event from the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA).

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA High Level Term

value.value: A superordinate descriptor for one or more Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA) preferred terms (PTs) for the adverse event.

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA High Level Term Code

value.value: A coded value specifying the high level term for the adverse event from the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA).

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA Low Level Term

value.value: Adverse event term related to the lowest level of the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA) terminology, related to a single PT as a synonym, lexical variant, or quasi-synonym.

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA Low Level Term Code

value.value: A coded value specifying the low level term for the adverse event from the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA).

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA Preferred Term Code

value.value: A coded value specifying the preferred term for the adverse event from the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA).

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA System Organ Class

value.value: Adverse event term related to the highest level of the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA) terminology, and distinguished by anatomical or physiological system, etiology, or purpose.

label.value: Adverse Event MedDRA Primary System Organ Class Code

value.value: A coded value specifying the primary system organ class for the adverse event from the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA).
An indication or description of a record that is considered to be the accepted and final evaluation for the disease response.
A classification of disease response data.

label.value: Date and Time of Disease Response Assessment

value.value: The date and time of disease response data collection.
The study day that a disease response assessment is performed.
A person who determines the significance of a disease response assessment.
A sequence of characters used to identify, name, or characterize the evaluator of the disease response.
A character or string that represents a disease response group.
A sequence of characters used to link multiple disease response records to a single finding.
A sequence of characters used as a linkage between related disease response records.
The literal identifier of the vendor or laboratory that performs a disease response assessment.
The outcome of the disease response assessment as originally received or collected.
The rationale why a disease response assessment was not performed.
A sequence of characters used to identify, name, or characterize the disease response reference.
A nitrogen mustard agent that crosslinks with DNA, causing inhibition of DNA synthesis. (NCI)
An identifier that describes the relative position of disease response data within a series.
One or more sponsor defined characters used to identify, name, or characterize the disease response assessment.
A term used to describe the state or condition of the completeness of the disease response data.

label.value: Disease Response Assessment Character Result in Standard Format

value.value: The standard character or string for representation and reporting of disease response data.
